        title: 'Mental Filter',
        content: `Definition:
You focus entirely on a single negative detail, dwelling on it exclusively so that your vision of all reality becomes darkened, like a drop of ink that discolors a beaker of water.

Everyday Examples:
1. Getting 9 positive performance reviews and 1 critical one, and only thinking about the critical one for days.
2. Having a great date, but focusing entirely on the moment you spilled a drop of water.
3. Enjoying a vacation but ruminating purely on the one day it rained.

How to challenge it:
1. Consciously list 3 positive things that happened in the same situation.
2. Ask yourself: "Am I filtering out the positives?"
3. Look at the "big picture" rather than the single drop of ink.`,
